The paper discusses the use of memristors for neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). It also discusses the properties of memristors as a type of perceptron, which could fall under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), architecture (cs.AR), electromagnetism (cs.EM), and machine learning (cs.LG).
